FBIS4-27859 "dreas108_d_94008" FBIS-EAS-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 South Korea Government Consults With Other Nations on DPRK Government Consults With Other Nations on DPRK Remittance of Money to North Viewed SK0606001394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 5 Jun 94 SK0606001394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [Report by YONHAP from Tokyo] [Text] NHK of Japan has reported that Japan notified the participants of the ROK, U.S., and Japan joint meeting held in Washington to discuss the North's nuclear issue that it is possible to discontinue Chongnyon [General Association of Korean Residents in Japan]-affiliated Korean-Japanese residents' remittance of money to North Korea. The broadcast noted that it was the first time the Japanese Government expressed an opinion about restricting the remittance of money to North Korea. It also added that the Japanese Government put forth its own proposal for imposing sanctions on North Korea, including restricting imports and exports and banning personal exchanges.
